article.headline: Northeastern 70, Delaware 61
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Matt Janning scored 18 points and made six assists and Bennet Davis added another 17 points and eight rebounds to help Northeastern to a 70-61 win Wednesday over Delaware. Bobby Kelly and Manny Adako each contributed another 10 points for the Huskies (11-18, 8-9 Colonial Athletic Association). Sam McMahon scored a game-high 24 points for Delaware (5-24, 3-14 CAA) and Herb Courtney scored 18 points and grabbed 14 rebounds. Brian Johnson added 17 points for the Blue Hens. Northeastern held the edge in rebounds, 37-31, while shooting 49.1 percent from the field (26 of 53), including 53.8 percent (14 of 26) in the second half when the Huskies pulled away.
